#  JavaScript Learning Repository

This repository contains all my JavaScript learning code, practice files, and mini projects as I progress from basics to advanced concepts.

🔗 Repo Link: https://github.com/Jenes-Sonkar/javascript-learning

---

##  About

This is my **personal JavaScript learning journey**, where I document everything I learn step by step.

It includes:

* Concept-wise folders
* Practice code
* DOM & Events
* Real-world mini projects

> A complete beginner-to-advanced JavaScript roadmap 🚀

---

##  Topics Covered

### 🔹 01 - Basics

* Variables (`let`, `const`, `var`)
* Data Types
* Type Conversion
* Memory (Stack vs Heap)

### 🔹 02 - Basics (Part 2)

* Strings
* Numbers & Math
* Date & Time

### 🔹 03 - Basics (Part 3)

* Arrays
* Objects
* Destructuring
* JSON APIs

### 🔹 04 - Control Flow

* `if-else`
* `switch`
* Comparisons

### 🔹 05 - Iterations

* `for`, `while`, `do-while`
* Loop control

### 🔹 06 - DOM

* DOM Selectors
* Manipulation
* Create/Edit/Delete elements

### 🔹 07 - Projects

* Mini JavaScript projects
* Hands-on practice

### 🔹 08 - Events

* Event listeners
* Event propagation

### 🔹 09 - Advanced JavaScript

* Closures
* Execution context
* Call stack
* Promises & async

### 🔹 10 - Classes & OOP

* Classes
* Constructors
* Prototypes
* Inheritance

### 🔹 11 - Fun with JS

* Advanced tricks
* Experiments

